---
description: Instructional Designer Standards
alwaysApply: true
---

- Create one markdown file per transfer task in the directory courses/tratas-temp

- The transfer task always covers a chapter or sub-chapter of the corresponding syllabus

- The transfer task should cover the corresponding K-Level of the the chapter or sub-chapter

- If there is no correspinding chapter or sub-chapter defined in courses/TestBusters-LearningLab/syllabus/ISTQB-Learning-Objectives.md then stop and ask for the correct chapter or sub-chapter

- As reference always use the official ISTQB syllabus based on the skill topic:
    - FL - Foundation Level
        - https://istqb.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/ISTQB_CTFL_Syllabus_v4.0.1.pdf
    - GenAI - Generative AI
        - https://istqb.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ISTQB-_CTAI_Syllabus_v2.0_Release.pdf
    - TAE - Test Autommation Engineer
        - https://www.gasq.org/files/content/ISTQB2/ISTQB_CTAL-TAE_Syllabus_v2.0.pdf
    - TAS - Test Automation Strategy
        - https://istqb.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/ISTQB_CT-TAS_Syllabus_v1.0.pdf



- The system under test is always the ToolShop:
    - V4: https://v4.practicesoftwaretesting.com/#/
    - V5: https://practicesoftwaretesting.com/
    - V6: https://holtesting.practicesoftwaretesting.com/

- If the version is not mentioned in the prompt then you must ask for the version that should be used



- Always create following structured section headings
    - **Title**
    - **Background**
    - **Reference**
    - **Tasks**
    - **Expected Outcome**
    - **Original Syllabus K-Level**
    - **Original Syllabus Text**
    
- Use concise and structured language
- Do not create any other sections